To develop a C++ program that reads a text file line by line and counts the number of occurrences of a specific word in the file, you can follow the structure below, which utilizes the `ifstream` class for reading files and the `stringstream` for parsing lines into individual words. 

Note that this program is case-sensitive to the word occurrences. If you need a case-insensitive count, you may want to convert the words to either all lower-case or all upper-case before comparison.

